This paper deals with communication complexity and information theory, which are both covered by cs.CC and cs.IT. The use of inner product as a gadget suggests that the paper may also be related to linear algebra and numerical analysis, which are covered by cs.DS and cs.NA. Finally, the paper discusses the use of randomness in protocols, which may be of interest to researchers in cryptography and security, covered by cs.CR.
